cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about speech recognition using a hybrid model consisting of CTC and attention encoder-decoder.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a novel CTC decoder structure and explores the relation between decoding performance and the depth of encoder.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses machine learning techniques for speech recognition.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with improving the performance of an end-to-end ASR system.
